yle="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-22_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-23_">Learn how to choose the right system, or combination, for scalable workforce development in regulated sectors.</h3><p class="sc-bhqpXc fHzOVK pf-25_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-107db706-50ae-470f-9e0b-f3f58e3db001"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Choosing the right digital systems is no longer a luxury. It's a strategic imperative when developing your workforce, staying compliant, and scaling internal training programmes. Yet the training technology landscape can feel overwhelming for organisations in regulated sectors such as healthcare, social care, and education.
<br><br>Two systems dominate the space: the Learning Management System (LMS) and the Training Management System (TMS). At first glance, they may appear similar. But in reality, each serves a distinct function, and understanding those differences is key to creating a high-performing, compliant, and future-ready learning function.
<br><br>In this blog, Elsie Rodas explores what sets LMS and TMS apart, why the distinction matters, and how you can build a smarter, more efficient training ecosystem that drives measurable impact across your organisation.
</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-28_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-29_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-30_">What is an LMS?</h3><p class="sc-bhqpXc fHzOVK pf-32_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-5d70b6f6-362e-46d8-a7e7-dc81678265a9"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">An LMS primarily focuses on delivering and tracking digital learning content. Think of it as the virtual classroom of your organisation, providing your team with anytime, anywhere access to learning materials such as:
</span></p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-35_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-36_">E-learning modules
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-38_">Instructional videos
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-40_">Reading resources
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-42_">Knowledge checks and quizzes
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-44_">Certificates of completion. 
</li></ul><p class="sc-bhqpXc fHzOVK pf-46_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-fbce96b3-cb5a-4fc9-8c98-b73ddc826807"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">An LMS supports individual learners by making it easy to access, progress through, and complete training. For L&amp;D and compliance teams, it also provides essential tracking capabilities, ensuring that every staff member has completed the required training and that documentation is up to date and audit-ready.
<br><br>However, LMS platforms are often learner-facing. They’re not built to manage the more complex, logistical side of training operations, especially when blended learning, internal trainers, or multiple locations are involved.
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-49_">What is a TMS?</h3><p class="sc-bhqpXc fHzOVK pf-51_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-25fd5eca-21a2-4ce8-a792-b8bcaee36eaa"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">A TMS is designed to support the administrative, operational, and reporting aspects of your organisation’s training activities. It’s the engine behind the scenes, built not for learners, but for the teams planning, scheduling, and evaluating training.
<br><br>Key functions of a TMS include:
</span></p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-54_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-55_">Scheduling and coordinating classroom, virtual, or hybrid sessions
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-57_">Assigning trainers and facilitators
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-59_">Managing venues, resources, and training equipment
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-61_">Tracking attendance, cancellations, and capacity
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-63_">Automating communications and reminders
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-65_">Producing reports for audits, inspections, and performance reviews. 
</li></ul><p class="sc-bhqpXc fHzOVK pf-67_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-2fae2f69-980f-4b50-a81e-cccd890f985d"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">While an LMS is focused on delivering content, a TMS is designed to run your training programme efficiently and strategically. This makes it an essential tool for organisations that must manage multiple training formats and compliance standards.
</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-70_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-71_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-72_">Why the LMS vs. TMS distinction matters in regulated sectors</h3><p class="sc-bhqpXc fHzOVK pf-74_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-9a91e08a-8d42-4dee-9ee1-d1003a0a4a10"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">In sectors like healthcare, education, social care, and public services, compliance isn’t optional. It’s central to day-to-day operations, and that includes training.
<br><br>Many organisations begin with an LMS to fulfil core e-learning and compliance requirements. It works well for ticking the boxes: assign the course, track the completion, and print the certificate.
<br><br>But as organisations scale, training programmes become more complex:
</span></p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-77_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-78_">New regulations require multi-format learning
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-80_">Internal trainers must be tracked and supported
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-82_">Face-to-face refreshers and competency assessments need coordination
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-84_">Regulators demand comprehensive, real-time reporting. 
</li></ul><p class="sc-bhqpXc fHzOVK pf-86_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-a8724f84-d9ab-446b-889d-9f47edc956da"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">That’s where the limitations of a standalone LMS become clear, and where the TMS becomes indispensable.
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-89_">Real-world scenarios - Where TMS makes the difference
</h3><p class="sc-bhqpXc fHzOVK pf-91_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-7406cb66-d354-4e99-a1bc-d32c617876fe"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">LMS platforms deliver content. TMS platforms manage everything around it - people, schedules, logistics, and compliance. Here's how:
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-94_">1. Coordinating in-person training across multiple sites</h3><p class="sc-bhqpXc fHzOVK pf-96_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-efc18d2d-361d-4137-9157-ece47280a270"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">A care home provider must deliver annual Moving and Handling refreshers for over 150 staff across several locations. While an LMS can host the theoretical content, it can’t manage the logistics, booking rooms, assigning trainers, or sending out session reminders. The TMS handles it all.
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-99_">2. Tracking internal trainers’ qualifications and workload</h3><p class="sc-bhqpXc fHzOVK pf-101_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-ba035376-d170-4af3-8a9b-62351025c805"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">A hospital trust is investing in upskilling staff as in-house trainers. The LMS can deliver AET Level 3 and other CPD courses, but only the TMS can manage their deployment, track sessions delivered, maintain certification records, and monitor trainer performance.
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-104_">3. Creating audit-ready compliance reports</h3><p class="sc-bhqpXc fHzOVK pf-106_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-af5a0b78-80d4-4e5b-81cb-1134e3ea0d82"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">An early years education provider must demonstrate staff training compliance during an Ofsted inspection. The LMS shows course completions, but the TMS pulls reports on attendance, CPD hours, staff qualifications, and session-level feedback, aligning everything with regulatory standards.
</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-109_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-110_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-111_">Do you need an LMS, a TMS, or both?</h3><p class="sc-bhqpXc fHzOVK pf-113_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-dd8b4e15-73ed-4877-b968-079ed01f79ef"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">In many cases, it’s not about choosing one or the other.<br><br>A robust training strategy often requires both systems working in harmony:
</span></p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-116_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-117_">Use an LMS to host, deliver, and track online learning
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-119_">Use a TMS to manage logistics, trainers, resources, and reporting.
</li></ul><p class="sc-bhqpXc fHzOVK pf-121_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-a8438ad0-19a7-413a-9ba3-566029dae85c"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Together, they create a unified training ecosystem, one that reduces administrative burden, supports blended delivery models, and ensures training is aligned with both internal goals and external regulations.<br><br>At The Mandatory Training Group, this integrated approach underpins our technology:
<br>
</span></p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-124_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-125_">ComplyPlus™ LMS delivers accredited e-learning, assessments, and certification
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-127_">ComplyPlus™ TMS coordinates scheduling, tracks trainer delivery, and automates performance reporting.
</li></ul><p class="sc-bhqpXc fHzOVK pf-129_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-e439e3b8-c510-4858-9ddf-f3ea29b3902a"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">The result? A seamless, centralised training solution trusted by providers across the UK’s regulated sectors.
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-132_">Key questions to ask before upgrading your system</h3><p class="sc-bhqpXc fHzOVK pf-134_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-f7fd95cd-54cb-4234-a1cd-7222058f8585"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">If you’re evaluating your current training setup, consider:</span></p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-137_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-138_">Are you delivering face-to-face or hybrid training that requires resource planning?
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-140_">Do you employ or contract internal trainers whose qualifications and workloads need monitoring?
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-142_">Are you preparing for CQC, Ofsted, or other external inspections?
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-144_">Is your current system causing spreadsheet overload or admin bottlenecks?
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-146_">Can you easily report on training effectiveness, compliance, and coverage across locations?
</li></ul><p class="sc-bhqpXc fHzOVK pf-148_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-9fc8ab3f-d7f1-43ec-84c5-0cfaacec569e"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">If the answer to any of these is no, a TMS, or a combined LMS/TMS solution, could be the key to closing those gaps.
</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-151_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-152_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-153_">Final thoughts - Build a system that grows with you</h3><p class="sc-bhqpXc fHzOVK pf-155_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-17150d33-073e-4dee-ac67-e3fe3befc2ee"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">A modern LMS is essential for digital delivery. But on its own, it’s not enough.
<br><br>Training today isn’t just about content. It’s about coordination, compliance, and outcomes. As your organisation’s workforce grows and regulatory pressures increase, your systems must evolve in tandem.<br><br>A TMS doesn’t replace your LMS. It complements and strengthens it. Together, these tools transform training from a compliance task into a powerful driver of staff development and organisational excellence.
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-158_">Ready to build a smarter training system?</h3><p class="sc-bhqpXc fHzOVK pf-160_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-14cf2cc8-370d-4a3c-8900-9241045ed6f1"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Struggling to coordinate in-person sessions, track internal trainers, or produce inspection-ready reports? You’re not alone.
